00:15:07.020 --> 00:15:08.760
They are all nonverbal.

00:15:08.760 --> 00:15:10.250
They are all nonverbal.

00:15:10.250 --> 00:15:12.150
How you look, how you
sound, how you move.

00:15:12.150 --> 00:15:14.480
And, if you're on a
stage, how you travel.

00:15:14.480 --> 00:15:17.310
And when we talk about
traveling on stage,

00:15:17.310 --> 00:15:20.420
it's not standing behind
a lectern, necessarily.

00:15:20.420 --> 00:15:23.510
It's about how you command
the room, or the stage,

00:15:23.510 --> 00:15:25.850
or the platform--
whatever you're on.

00:15:25.850 --> 00:15:30.150
And then voice is
part of how you sound,

00:15:30.150 --> 00:15:33.130
and it's in a
category by itself.

00:15:33.130 --> 00:15:38.140
So let's talk a little bit about
each of the nonverbal codes.

00:15:38.140 --> 00:15:42.060
And we call them codes
because they are exactly that.

00:15:44.740 --> 00:15:47.230
They are simply not using words.

00:15:47.230 --> 00:15:50.210
How we communicate
without using words.

00:15:50.210 --> 00:15:54.190
So one of the big things
that we've heard about

00:15:54.190 --> 00:15:57.460
is Bernie Sanders
