00:37:56.540 --> 00:38:00.060
And then, of course, we've
got Make America Great

00:38:00.060 --> 00:38:03.040
Again, which you
many of you knew.

00:38:03.040 --> 00:38:04.990
So let's just break that down.

00:38:04.990 --> 00:38:06.970
What is a slogan?

00:38:06.970 --> 00:38:10.330
A slogan is a
combination of words

00:38:10.330 --> 00:38:16.210
that is framed in a way that
has an emotional impact.

00:38:16.210 --> 00:38:19.350
Framing is a way of
inserting a point of view

00:38:19.350 --> 00:38:22.120
into one word or a few words.

00:38:22.120 --> 00:38:25.450
And we want to keep
an economy of words,

00:38:25.450 --> 00:38:28.700
but it's not ultimately
necessary, always necessary,

00:38:28.700 --> 00:38:31.110
for it to be a very few words.

00:38:31.110 --> 00:38:34.080
My favorite one-word
frame right now

00:38:34.080 --> 00:38:37.130
is Democrat as an adjective.

00:38:37.130 --> 00:38:41.440
Democrat congress, Democrat
president, Democrat idea,

00:38:41.440 --> 00:38:43.290
as opposed to "democratic."

00:38:43.290 --> 00:38:46.340
That's a very interesting frame.

00:38:46.340 --> 00:38:47.780
Make America Great Again.

00:38:47.780 --> 00:38:50.810
This is what I call a
"God Damn It" statement.

00:38:50.810 --> 00:38:52.790
It's a God Damn It statement.

00:38:52.790 --> 00:38:56.510
So let's do an
analysis of the words.

00:38:56.510 --> 00:38:57.971
Make-- it's a command.

00:38:57.971 --> 00:38:58.470
Right?

00:38:58.470 --> 00:38:58.930
Make.

00:38:58.930 --> 00:38:59.770
We're going to make.

00:38:59.770 --> 00:39:02.010
I'll make, you make, we make.

00:39:02.010 --> 00:39:05.910
America-- self-explanatory,
the country, our great country.

00:39:05.910 --> 00:39:09.810
Great-- great, everybody
thinks of America as great,

00:39:09.810 --> 00:39:12.400
or we want to think
of America as great.

00:39:12.400 --> 00:39:15.020
Not everybody does, but
we want to, we hope to,

00:39:15.020 --> 00:39:16.460
we aspire to that.

00:39:16.460 --> 00:39:19.170
And then, Again-- ah,
that's the key word.

00:39:19.170 --> 00:39:20.480
That's the key word, "again."

00:39:20.480 --> 00:39:22.580
America was great once.

00:39:22.580 --> 00:39:24.440
It isn't any more.

00:39:24.440 --> 00:39:28.620
And go with Donald Trump,
it'll be great again.

00:39:28.620 --> 00:39:31.330
Stick with me, and
it will happen again.

00:39:31.330 --> 00:39:32.680
So this is a frame.

00:39:32.680 --> 00:39:33.290
It's a frame.

00:39:33.290 --> 00:39:36.600
The other thing that
happens with this slogan

00:39:36.600 --> 00:39:39.200
is the way the word
endings and beginnings are.

00:39:39.200 --> 00:39:42.210
So "make America--" ck ah.

00:39:42.210 --> 00:39:45.020
So the end of "make"
is a "ck" sound.

00:39:45.020 --> 00:39:47.020
And then America
is a vowel, right?

00:39:47.020 --> 00:39:49.490
It's a short "a."

00:39:49.490 --> 00:39:51.760
So "make America" flows.

00:39:51.760 --> 00:39:54.010
"Great." "Make America great."

00:39:54.010 --> 00:39:58.480
Eh, that's a little bit
different, not as smooth.

00:39:58.480 --> 00:40:00.380
But "great again."

00:40:00.380 --> 00:40:01.460
So it flows.

00:40:01.460 --> 00:40:04.560
It rolls off the
tongue really easily.

00:40:04.560 --> 00:40:06.880
So this is what Trump does.

00:40:06.880 --> 00:40:09.050
And he does it very, very well.

00:40:09.050 --> 00:40:14.240
And the other thing that
he does, is he keeps it,

00:40:14.240 --> 00:40:16.190
he repeats it all the time.

00:40:16.190 --> 00:40:17.950
This is called
"message discipline."

00:40:17.950 --> 00:40:18.900
It's on his hat.

00:40:18.900 --> 00:40:21.970
He does it on his Insta.

00:40:21.970 --> 00:40:23.540
Anybody connected
with his Instagram?

00:40:23.540 --> 00:40:25.206
Do you follow him on Insta?

00:40:25.206 --> 00:40:26.769
Oh, he's amazing.

00:40:26.769 --> 00:40:27.310
Just amazing.

00:40:27.310 --> 00:40:30.770
He blows me away as a
media-- he's media expert.

00:40:30.770 --> 00:40:34.650
He's a genius at keeping
himself in the public eye,

00:40:34.650 --> 00:40:37.320
on the front page, getting ink.

00:40:37.320 --> 00:40:40.000
In fact, the journalists
I talk to complain

00:40:40.000 --> 00:40:43.800
that because media is so
corporate at this point,

00:40:43.800 --> 00:40:47.250
they keep Donald Trump in the
news because it sells papers,

00:40:47.250 --> 00:40:49.070
and it sells advertising time.

00:40:49.070 --> 00:40:53.612
This is a sad but true thing
about our media industry.

00:40:53.612 --> 00:40:54.820
They should be protecting us.

00:40:54.820 --> 00:40:56.528
I don't think they're
doing as good a job

00:40:56.528 --> 00:40:57.920
as they should with this.

00:40:57.920 --> 00:41:00.030
So "Make America Great
Again," a God Damn It

00:41:00.030 --> 00:41:04.530
statement that rolls off
the tongue really easily.

