And start thinking about,
also, the message discipline.

00:45:07.110 --> 00:45:09.870
Repeating it over and
over and over again.

00:45:09.870 --> 00:45:13.012
We want it to be aspirational,
and you want to repeat it.

00:45:13.012 --> 00:45:14.720
By the way, test it,
and you'll see this.

00:45:14.720 --> 00:45:19.350
Just like we saw with Marco
Rubio's-- I think it was this

00:45:19.350 --> 00:45:20.195
last one.

00:45:20.195 --> 00:45:21.570
Nope, that was
"I'm with stupid."

00:45:21.570 --> 00:45:22.390
Sorry.

00:45:22.390 --> 00:45:24.590
Here we go.

00:45:24.590 --> 00:45:28.260
You know, with Rubio, he's
testing this new piece of it.

00:45:28.260 --> 00:45:30.300
He's putting it into a question.

00:45:30.300 --> 00:45:32.570
But before, it was just
"A New American Century."

00:45:32.570 --> 00:45:33.250
He's testing it.

00:45:33.250 --> 00:45:33.750
We'll see.

00:45:33.750 --> 00:45:36.050
So they test things,
just like we do,

00:45:36.050 --> 00:45:38.820
just like you do, in
business to see what works.

00:45:42.020 --> 00:45:42.730
All right.

00:45:42.730 --> 00:45:46.660
Let's go to the
personal narrative.

00:45:46.660 --> 00:45:48.320
AUDIENCE: One other
thing. [INAUDIBLE]

00:45:48.320 --> 00:45:53.765
