00:46:09.479 --> 00:46:10.520
RUTH SHERMAN: Absolutely.

00:46:10.520 --> 00:46:14.010
It's a simple frame, but I
think, you know, it's not new.

00:46:14.010 --> 00:46:16.110
It's not a new
combination of words.

00:46:16.110 --> 00:46:18.640
In fact, it was used around
the Reagan Administration.

00:46:18.640 --> 00:46:21.520
They framed it, or when Ronald
Reagan was running for office.

00:46:21.520 --> 00:46:24.230
There are only so many
words, simple words,

00:46:24.230 --> 00:46:28.630
and simple declarative
statements, that exists,

00:46:28.630 --> 00:46:32.100
that will work in
these contexts.

00:46:32.100 --> 00:46:34.690
But I think it's his discipline.

00:46:34.690 --> 00:46:36.870
He found an excellent
combination of words.

00:46:36.870 --> 00:46:38.350
This was not an accident.

00:46:38.350 --> 00:46:40.450
It was a good frame.

00:46:40.450 --> 00:46:42.600
And he repeats it ad infinitum.

00:46:42.600 --> 00:46:44.220
He repeats it constantly.

00:46:44.220 --> 00:46:45.974
Let's see what I got here.

